This branch addresses two main things:

1) Time Dependent Operators are defined (see TimeDepOpers.cpp and TimeDepOpers.hpp).
These allow for different time stepping algorithms to be selected/used in the simulations 
without having to define the appropriate matrices manually. 
This is accomplished with a user-defined explicit step and implicit step. 
MFEM then builds all other algorithms based on these.
The Time Dependent Operators are utilized in the simulation code BESFEM_2D_Par.cpp.

2) The process for taking Voxel input and outputting a Distance Function 
is demonstrated in VoxelToDistFunc.cpp.  The Distance Function defines the complex geometry
and is used to define the Order Parameter (psi) in the simulation equations.
NOTE: THIS CODE IS CURRENTLY UNDER DEVELOPMENT AND SHOULD BE COMPLETED SOON.
